{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This cell phone"},{"time":3000,"text":"started its trajectory"},{"time":6000,"text":"in an artisanal mine"},{"time":8000,"text":"in the Eastern Congo."},{"time":10000,"text":"It's mined by armed gangs"},{"time":12000,"text":"using slaves, child slaves,"},{"time":14000,"text":"what the U.N. Security Council"},{"time":16000,"text":"calls \"blood minerals,\""},{"time":18000,"text":"then traveled into some components"},{"time":20000,"text":"and ended up in a factory"},{"time":22000,"text":"in Shinjin in China."},{"time":24000,"text":"That factory -- over a dozen people have committed suicide"},{"time":27000,"text":"already this year."},{"time":29000,"text":"One man died after working a 36-hour shift."},{"time":33000,"text":"We all love chocolate."},{"time":35000,"text":"We buy it for our kids."},{"time":37000,"text":"Eighty percent of the cocoa comes from Cote d'Ivoire and Ghana"},{"time":40000,"text":"and it's harvested by children."},{"time":43000,"text":"Cote d'Ivoire, we have a huge problem of child slaves."},{"time":45000,"text":"Children have been trafficked from other conflict zones"},{"time":48000,"text":"to come and work on the coffee plantations."},{"time":51000,"text":"Heparin -- a blood thinner,"},{"time":53000,"text":"a pharmaceutical product --"},{"time":55000,"text":"starts out in artisanal workshops"},{"time":58000,"text":"like this in China,"},{"time":60000,"text":"because the active ingredient"},{"time":62000,"text":"comes from pigs' intestines."},{"time":65000,"text":"Your diamond -- you've all heard, probably seen the movie \"Blood Diamond.\""},{"time":68000,"text":"This is a mine in Zimbabwe"},{"time":70000,"text":"right now."},{"time":72000,"text":"Cotton: Uzbekistan is the second biggest"},{"time":74000,"text":"exporter of cotton on Earth."},{"time":76000,"text":"Every year when it comes to the cotton harvest,"},{"time":79000,"text":"the government shuts down the schools,"},{"time":81000,"text":"puts the kids in buses, buses them to the cotton fields"},{"time":84000,"text":"to spend three weeks harvesting the cotton."},{"time":87000,"text":"It's forced child labor"},{"time":89000,"text":"on an institutional scale."},{"time":92000,"text":"And all of those products probably end their lives"},{"time":95000,"text":"in a dump like this one in Manila."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"These places, these origins,"},{"time":100000,"text":"represent governance gaps."},{"time":102000,"text":"That's the politest description"},{"time":104000,"text":"I have for them."},{"time":107000,"text":"These are the dark pools"},{"time":109000,"text":"where global supply chains begin --"},{"time":112000,"text":"the global supply chains,"},{"time":114000,"text":"which bring us our favorite brand name products."},{"time":117000,"text":"Some of these governance gaps"},{"time":120000,"text":"are run by rogue states."},{"time":123000,"text":"Some of them are not states anymore at all."},{"time":125000,"text":"They're failed states."},{"time":127000,"text":"Some of them"},{"time":129000,"text":"are just countries who believe that deregulation or no regulation"},{"time":132000,"text":"is the best way to attract investment,"},{"time":135000,"text":"promote trade."},{"time":137000,"text":"Either way, they present us"},{"time":139000,"text":"with a huge moral and ethical dilemma."},{"time":143000,"text":"I know that none of us want to be accessories"},{"time":145000,"text":"after the fact"},{"time":148000,"text":"of a human rights abuse"},{"time":150000,"text":"in a global supply chain."},{"time":152000,"text":"But right now,"},{"time":154000,"text":"most of the companies involved in these supply chains"},{"time":157000,"text":"don't have any way"},{"time":159000,"text":"of assuring us"},{"time":161000,"text":"that nobody had to mortgage their future,"},{"time":163000,"text":"nobody had to sacrifice their rights"},{"time":166000,"text":"to bring us our favorite"},{"time":168000,"text":"brand name product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"Now, I didn't come here to depress you"},{"time":173000,"text":"about the state of the global supply chain."},{"time":176000,"text":"We need a reality check."},{"time":178000,"text":"We need to recognize just how serious"},{"time":181000,"text":"a deficit of rights we have."},{"time":184000,"text":"This is an independent republic,"},{"time":186000,"text":"probably a failed state."},{"time":188000,"text":"It's definitely not a democratic state."},{"time":192000,"text":"And right now,"},{"time":194000,"text":"that independent republic of the supply chain"},{"time":196000,"text":"is not being governed"},{"time":198000,"text":"in a way that would satisfy us,"},{"time":201000,"text":"that we can engage in ethical trade or ethical consumption."},{"time":205000,"text":"Now, that's not a new story."},{"time":207000,"text":"You've seen the documentaries"},{"time":209000,"text":"of sweatshops making garments"},{"time":211000,"text":"all over the world, even in developed countries."},{"time":214000,"text":"You want to see the classic sweatshop,"},{"time":216000,"text":"meet me at Madison Square Garden,"},{"time":218000,"text":"I'll take you down the street, and I'll show you a Chinese sweatshop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"But take the example of heparin."},{"time":224000,"text":"It's a pharmaceutical product."},{"time":226000,"text":"You expect that the supply chain that gets it to the hospital,"},{"time":229000,"text":"probably squeaky clean."},{"time":233000,"text":"The problem is that the active ingredient in there --"},{"time":235000,"text":"as I mentioned earlier --"},{"time":237000,"text":"comes from pigs."},{"time":239000,"text":"The main American manufacturer"},{"time":242000,"text":"of that active ingredient"},{"time":244000,"text":"decided a few years ago to relocate to China"},{"time":247000,"text":"because it's the world's biggest supplier of pigs."},{"time":250000,"text":"And their factory in China --"},{"time":252000,"text":"which probably is pretty clean --"},{"time":255000,"text":"is getting all of the ingredients"},{"time":257000,"text":"from backyard abattoirs,"},{"time":259000,"text":"where families slaughter pigs"},{"time":261000,"text":"and extract the ingredient."},{"time":264000,"text":"So a couple of years ago, we had a scandal"},{"time":266000,"text":"which killed about 80 people around the world,"},{"time":268000,"text":"because of contaminants"},{"time":270000,"text":"that crept into the heparin supply chain."},{"time":273000,"text":"Worse, some of the suppliers"},{"time":275000,"text":"realized that they could substitute a product"},{"time":279000,"text":"which mimicked heparin in tests."},{"time":283000,"text":"This substitute cost nine dollars a pound,"},{"time":286000,"text":"whereas real heparin, the real ingredient,"},{"time":289000,"text":"cost 900 dollars a pound."},{"time":292000,"text":"A no-brainer."},{"time":294000,"text":"The problem was that it killed more people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"And so you're asking yourself,"},{"time":299000,"text":"\"How come the U.S. Food and Drug Administration"},{"time":301000,"text":"allowed this to happen?"},{"time":303000,"text":"How did the Chinese State Agency for Food and Drugs"},{"time":305000,"text":"allow this to happen?\""},{"time":307000,"text":"And the answer is quite simple:"},{"time":310000,"text":"the Chinese define these facilities"},{"time":312000,"text":"as chemical facilities, not pharmaceutical facilities,"},{"time":315000,"text":"so they don't audit them."},{"time":317000,"text":"And the USFDA"},{"time":319000,"text":"has a jurisdictional problem."},{"time":321000,"text":"This is offshore."},{"time":323000,"text":"They actually do conduct a few investigations overseas --"},{"time":325000,"text":"about a dozen a year -- maybe 20 in a good year."},{"time":328000,"text":"There are 500"},{"time":330000,"text":"of these facilities"},{"time":332000,"text":"producing active ingredients in China alone."},{"time":335000,"text":"In fact, about 80 percent"},{"time":338000,"text":"of the active ingredients in medicines now"},{"time":340000,"text":"come from offshore,"},{"time":342000,"text":"particularly China and India,"},{"time":344000,"text":"and we don't have a governance system."},{"time":347000,"text":"We don't have a regulatory system"},{"time":349000,"text":"able to ensure"},{"time":351000,"text":"that that production is safe."},{"time":355000,"text":"We don't have a system to ensure"},{"time":357000,"text":"that human rights, basic dignity,"},{"time":359000,"text":"are ensured."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"So at a national level --"},{"time":365000,"text":"and we work in about 60 different countries --"},{"time":367000,"text":"at a national level"},{"time":369000,"text":"we've got a serious breakdown in the ability of governments"},{"time":371000,"text":"to regulate production"},{"time":374000,"text":"on their own soil."},{"time":377000,"text":"And the real problem with the global supply chain"},{"time":379000,"text":"is that it's supranational."},{"time":381000,"text":"So governments who are failing,"},{"time":383000,"text":"who are dropping the ball"},{"time":385000,"text":"at a national level,"},{"time":387000,"text":"have even less ability to get their arms around the problem"},{"time":389000,"text":"at an international level."},{"time":392000,"text":"And you can just look at the headlines."},{"time":394000,"text":"Take Copenhagen last year --"},{"time":397000,"text":"complete failure of governments"},{"time":399000,"text":"to do the right thing"},{"time":401000,"text":"in the face of an international challenge."},{"time":404000,"text":"Take the G20 meeting a couple of weeks ago --"},{"time":407000,"text":"stepped back from its commitments of just a few months ago."},{"time":412000,"text":"You can take any one"},{"time":414000,"text":"of the major global challenges we've discussed this week"},{"time":417000,"text":"and ask yourself, where is the leadership from governments"},{"time":420000,"text":"to step up and come up with solutions,"},{"time":423000,"text":"responses,"},{"time":425000,"text":"to those international problems?"},{"time":428000,"text":"And the simple answer is they can't. They're national."},{"time":432000,"text":"Their voters are local."},{"time":434000,"text":"They have parochial interests."},{"time":436000,"text":"They can't subordinate those interests"},{"time":438000,"text":"to the greater global public good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441000,"text":"So, if we're going to ensure the delivery"},{"time":443000,"text":"of the key public goods"},{"time":445000,"text":"at an international level --"},{"time":447000,"text":"in this case, in the global supply chain --"},{"time":450000,"text":"we have to come up with a different mechanism."},{"time":453000,"text":"We need a different machine."},{"time":457000,"text":"Fortunately, we have some examples."},{"time":461000,"text":"In the 1990s,"},{"time":463000,"text":"there were a whole series of scandals"},{"time":465000,"text":"concerning the production of brand name goods in the U.S. --"},{"time":467000,"text":"child labor, forced labor,"},{"time":469000,"text":"serious health and safety abuses."},{"time":472000,"text":"And eventually President Clinton, in 1996,"},{"time":474000,"text":"convened a meeting at the White House,"},{"time":477000,"text":"invited industry, human rights NGOs,"},{"time":480000,"text":"trade unions, the Department of Labor,"},{"time":482000,"text":"got them all in a room"},{"time":484000,"text":"and said, \"Look,"},{"time":486000,"text":"I don't want globalization to be a race to the bottom."},{"time":488000,"text":"I don't know how to prevent that,"},{"time":490000,"text":"but I'm at least going to use my good offices"},{"time":492000,"text":"to get you folks together"},{"time":494000,"text":"to come up with a response.\""},{"time":497000,"text":"So they formed a White House task force,"},{"time":499000,"text":"and they spent about three years arguing"},{"time":502000,"text":"about who takes how much responsibility"},{"time":505000,"text":"in the global supply chain."},{"time":508000,"text":"Companies didn't feel it was their responsibility."},{"time":511000,"text":"They don't own those facilities."},{"time":513000,"text":"They don't employ those workers."},{"time":515000,"text":"They're not legally liable."},{"time":518000,"text":"Everybody else at the table"},{"time":520000,"text":"said, \"Folks, that doesn't cut it."},{"time":522000,"text":"You have a custodial duty, a duty of care,"},{"time":525000,"text":"to make sure that that product"},{"time":527000,"text":"gets from wherever to the store"},{"time":530000,"text":"in a way that allows us to consume it,"},{"time":533000,"text":"without fear of our safety,"},{"time":536000,"text":"or without having to sacrifice our conscience"},{"time":540000,"text":"to consume that product.\""},{"time":542000,"text":"So they agreed, \"Okay, what we'll do"},{"time":545000,"text":"is we agree on a common set of standards,"},{"time":547000,"text":"code of conduct."},{"time":549000,"text":"We'll apply that throughout"},{"time":551000,"text":"our global supply chain"},{"time":553000,"text":"regardless of ownership or control."},{"time":555000,"text":"We'll make it part of the contract.\""},{"time":558000,"text":"And that was a stroke of absolute genius,"},{"time":561000,"text":"because what they did"},{"time":563000,"text":"was they harnessed the power of the contract,"},{"time":566000,"text":"private power,"},{"time":568000,"text":"to deliver public goods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"And let's face it,"},{"time":572000,"text":"the contract from a major multinational brand"},{"time":574000,"text":"to a supplier in India or China"},{"time":577000,"text":"has much more persuasive value"},{"time":579000,"text":"than the local labor law,"},{"time":581000,"text":"the local environmental regulations,"},{"time":583000,"text":"the local human rights standards."},{"time":586000,"text":"Those factories will probably never see an inspector."},{"time":589000,"text":"If the inspector did come along,"},{"time":592000,"text":"it would be amazing if they were able"},{"time":594000,"text":"to resist the bribe."},{"time":598000,"text":"Even if they did their jobs,"},{"time":600000,"text":"and they cited those facilities for their violations,"},{"time":604000,"text":"the fine would be derisory."},{"time":606000,"text":"But you lose that contract"},{"time":608000,"text":"for a major brand name,"},{"time":610000,"text":"that's the difference"},{"time":612000,"text":"between staying in business or going bankrupt."},{"time":615000,"text":"That makes a difference."},{"time":617000,"text":"So what we've been able to do"},{"time":619000,"text":"is we've been able to harness"},{"time":621000,"text":"the power and the influence"},{"time":623000,"text":"of the only truly transnational institution"},{"time":626000,"text":"in the global supply chain,"},{"time":628000,"text":"that of the multinational company,"},{"time":631000,"text":"and get them to do the right thing,"},{"time":633000,"text":"get them to use that power for good,"},{"time":636000,"text":"to deliver the key public goods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640000,"text":"Now of course, this doesn't come naturally"},{"time":642000,"text":"to multinational companies."},{"time":644000,"text":"They weren't set up to do this. They're set up to make money."},{"time":647000,"text":"But they are extremely efficient organizations."},{"time":650000,"text":"They have resources,"},{"time":652000,"text":"and if we can add the will, the commitment,"},{"time":655000,"text":"they know how to deliver that product."},{"time":660000,"text":"Now, getting there is not easy."},{"time":663000,"text":"Those supply chains I put up on the screen earlier,"},{"time":666000,"text":"they're not there."},{"time":668000,"text":"You need a safe space."},{"time":670000,"text":"You need a place where people can come together,"},{"time":673000,"text":"sit down without fear of judgment,"},{"time":675000,"text":"without recrimination,"},{"time":677000,"text":"to actually face the problem,"},{"time":679000,"text":"agree on the problem and come up with solutions."},{"time":682000,"text":"We can do it. The technical solutions are there."},{"time":685000,"text":"The problem is the lack of trust, the lack of confidence,"},{"time":688000,"text":"the lack of partnership"},{"time":690000,"text":"between NGOs, campaign groups,"},{"time":692000,"text":"civil society organizations"},{"time":695000,"text":"and multinational companies."},{"time":698000,"text":"If we can put those two together in a safe space,"},{"time":701000,"text":"get them to work together,"},{"time":703000,"text":"we can deliver public goods right now,"},{"time":706000,"text":"or in extremely short supply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709000,"text":"This is a radical proposition,"},{"time":711000,"text":"and it's crazy to think"},{"time":713000,"text":"that if you're a 15-year-old Bangladeshi girl"},{"time":716000,"text":"leaving your rural village"},{"time":719000,"text":"to go and work in a factory in Dhaka --"},{"time":722000,"text":"22, 23, 24 dollars a month --"},{"time":727000,"text":"your best chance of enjoying rights at work"},{"time":730000,"text":"is if that factory is producing"},{"time":732000,"text":"for a brand name company"},{"time":734000,"text":"which has got a code of conduct"},{"time":736000,"text":"and made that code of conduct part of the contract."},{"time":740000,"text":"It's crazy."},{"time":742000,"text":"Multinationals are protecting human rights."},{"time":744000,"text":"I know there's going to be disbelief."},{"time":746000,"text":"You'll say, \"How can we trust them?\""},{"time":748000,"text":"Well, we don't."},{"time":750000,"text":"It's the old arms control phrase:"},{"time":752000,"text":"\"Trust, but verify.\""},{"time":754000,"text":"So we audit."},{"time":756000,"text":"We take their supply chain, we take all the factory names,"},{"time":759000,"text":"we do a random sample,"},{"time":761000,"text":"we send inspectors on an unannounced basis"},{"time":764000,"text":"to inspect those facilities,"},{"time":766000,"text":"and then we publish the results."},{"time":768000,"text":"Transparency is absolutely critical to this."},{"time":772000,"text":"You can call yourself responsible,"},{"time":775000,"text":"but responsibility without accountability"},{"time":778000,"text":"often doesn't work."},{"time":780000,"text":"So what we're doing is, we're not only enlisting the multinationals,"},{"time":783000,"text":"we're giving them the tools to deliver this public good --"},{"time":786000,"text":"respect for human rights --"},{"time":788000,"text":"and we're checking."},{"time":790000,"text":"You don't need to believe me. You shouldn't believe me."},{"time":792000,"text":"Go to the website. Look at the audit results."},{"time":795000,"text":"Ask yourself, is this company behaving"},{"time":797000,"text":"in a socially responsible way?"},{"time":800000,"text":"Can I buy that product"},{"time":802000,"text":"without compromising my ethics?"},{"time":805000,"text":"That's the way the system works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"I hate the idea"},{"time":812000,"text":"that governments are not protecting human rights around the world."},{"time":815000,"text":"I hate the idea"},{"time":817000,"text":"that governments have dropped this ball"},{"time":819000,"text":"and I can't get used to the idea"},{"time":822000,"text":"that somehow we can't get them to do their jobs."},{"time":825000,"text":"I've been at this for 30 years,"},{"time":827000,"text":"and in that time I've seen"},{"time":829000,"text":"the ability, the commitment, the will of government"},{"time":832000,"text":"to do this decline,"},{"time":834000,"text":"and I don't see them making a comeback right now."},{"time":837000,"text":"So we started out thinking"},{"time":839000,"text":"this was a stopgap measure."},{"time":841000,"text":"We're now thinking that, in fact,"},{"time":844000,"text":"this is probably the start"},{"time":846000,"text":"of a new way of regulating and addressing"},{"time":849000,"text":"international challenges."},{"time":851000,"text":"Call it network governance. Call it what you will."},{"time":854000,"text":"The private actors,"},{"time":857000,"text":"companies and NGOs,"},{"time":859000,"text":"are going to have to get together"},{"time":861000,"text":"to face the major challenges we are going to face."},{"time":863000,"text":"Just look at pandemics --"},{"time":865000,"text":"swine flu, bird flu, H1N1."},{"time":868000,"text":"Look at the health systems in so many countries."},{"time":870000,"text":"Do they have the resources"},{"time":872000,"text":"to face up to a serious pandemic?"},{"time":875000,"text":"No."},{"time":877000,"text":"Could the private sector and NGOs"},{"time":880000,"text":"get together and marshal a response?"},{"time":882000,"text":"Absolutely."},{"time":884000,"text":"What they lack is that safe space"},{"time":886000,"text":"to come together, agree"},{"time":888000,"text":"and move to action."},{"time":890000,"text":"That's what we're trying to provide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"I know as well"},{"time":896000,"text":"that this often seems"},{"time":898000,"text":"like an overwhelming level of responsibility"},{"time":900000,"text":"for people to assume."},{"time":902000,"text":"\"You want me to deliver human rights"},{"time":904000,"text":"throughout my global supply chain."},{"time":906000,"text":"There are thousands of suppliers in there.\""},{"time":909000,"text":"It seems too daunting, too dangerous,"},{"time":912000,"text":"for any company to take on."},{"time":914000,"text":"But there are companies."},{"time":916000,"text":"We have 4,000 companies who are members."},{"time":919000,"text":"Some of them are very, very large companies."},{"time":921000,"text":"The sporting goods industry, in particular,"},{"time":923000,"text":"stepped up to the plate and have done it."},{"time":926000,"text":"The example, the role model, is there."},{"time":930000,"text":"And whenever we discuss"},{"time":932000,"text":"one of these problems that we have to address --"},{"time":934000,"text":"child labor in cottonseed farms in India --"},{"time":937000,"text":"this year we will monitor 50,000 cottonseed farms in India."},{"time":941000,"text":"It seems overwhelming."},{"time":943000,"text":"The numbers just make you want to zone out."},{"time":946000,"text":"But we break it down to some basic realities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949000,"text":"And human rights"},{"time":951000,"text":"comes down to a very simple proposition:"},{"time":954000,"text":"can I give this person their dignity back?"},{"time":957000,"text":"Poor people,"},{"time":959000,"text":"people whose human rights have been violated --"},{"time":961000,"text":"the crux of that"},{"time":963000,"text":"is the loss of dignity,"},{"time":965000,"text":"the lack of dignity."},{"time":967000,"text":"It starts with just giving people back their dignity."},{"time":970000,"text":"I was sitting in a slum outside Gurgaon"},{"time":973000,"text":"just next to Delhi,"},{"time":975000,"text":"one of the flashiest, brightest new cities"},{"time":978000,"text":"popping up in India right now,"},{"time":981000,"text":"and I was talking to workers"},{"time":983000,"text":"who worked in garment sweatshops down the road,"},{"time":985000,"text":"and I asked them what message they would like me to take to the brands."},{"time":989000,"text":"They didn't say money."},{"time":992000,"text":"They said, \"The people who employ us"},{"time":995000,"text":"treat us like we are less than human,"},{"time":998000,"text":"like we don't exist."},{"time":1000000,"text":"Please ask them to treat us like human beings.\""},{"time":1004000,"text":"That's my simple understanding of human rights."},{"time":1006000,"text":"That's my simple proposition to you,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"my simple plea to every decision-maker"},{"time":1012000,"text":"in this room, everybody out there."},{"time":1014000,"text":"We can all make a decision"},{"time":1016000,"text":"to come together"},{"time":1018000,"text":"and pick up the balls and run with the balls"},{"time":1021000,"text":"that governments have dropped."},{"time":1023000,"text":"If we don't do it,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"we're abandoning hope,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"we're abandoning our essential humanity,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"and I know that's not a place we want to be,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"and we don't have to be there."},{"time":1034000,"text":"So I appeal to you."},{"time":1036000,"text":"Join us, come into that safe space,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"and let's start to make this happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}